==French==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[appellare]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/apəle/}}

===Verb===
'''appeler'''

# (''transitive'') to [[call]] (out)
#:''J'ai appelé son nom.''  I called out her name.
# (''transitive'') to [[call]], [[phone]], [[ring]]
#:''Appelle-moi ce soir.''  Call me this evening.
# (''transitive'') to [[call]] for, [[summon]]
#:''Nous devrons appeler un médecin.''  We should call a doctor.
# (''intransitive'') to [[call]] (out)
#:''Elle a appelé à l'aide.''  She called out for help.
'''s'appeler'''
# (''reflexive'') to be called
#:''Je m'appelle James.''  I'm called James.

===Conjugation===
{{fr-conj-xx-er|appe|l}}

